Post.title: RMac - install rJava, xlsx Package
Post._content:
xlsxexcelReporteRswordrJavarJava.

### step1 -  

1.  jre[https://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jre8-downloads-2133155.html](https://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jre8-downloads-2133155.html)
2.  jdk[https://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html](https://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html)
3.  termina java version 2

### step2 - 

1.  terminal open -e .bash\_profile  touch.bash\_profile  6 JAVA\_HOME=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.8.0\_181.jdk/Contents/Home PATH=$JAVA\_HOME/bin:$PATH:. CLASSPATH=$JAVA\_HOME/lib/tools.jar:$JAVA\_HOME/lib/dt.jar:. export JAVA\_HOME export PATH export CLASSPATH
2.  terminal source ~/.bash_profile

### step3 - R

1.  terminal
2.  sudo R CMD javareconf
3.  r install.packages('rJava')
4.  terminal  sudo ln -f -s $(/usr/libexec/java_home)/jre/lib/server/libjvm.dylib /usr/local/lib

 ,oracleJDKsudo R CMD javareconf
